						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1591 (1669 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers gift of land in Umayāpuram and Pirappaṅguḍi by Aḻagiri, son of Chennama-Nāyaka of the Janakala-gōtra, for offerings and worship to the god on the 2nd day of the Bhūpati-Uḍaiyār festival, when the god was taken to the Viṭṭhalarājar-maṇḍapa. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1591, Saumya, Tulā, śu. 3, Sunday, Anusham,</hi> corresponds regularly to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1669, October 17, Sunday; ·81; ·43.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
